test.impression:
Slight interval decrease in size of right-sided pneumothorax;
 however, interval enlargement of the right-sided pleural effusion.  Stable
 mild leftward deviation of the cardiomediastinal silhouette.

1. Cardiomegaly with worsening pulmonary edema.
 2. Subtle left suprahilar nodular opacity may represent a focal area of edema;
 repeat imaging after diuresis may be considered.
